																				<div class="sg-editor">
						
<p>Are you experiencing sore, tight, and stiff shoulders that restrict your movement in the gym and daily life? Then it’s time to start incorporating shoulder mobility exercises into your training.</p>



<p>The shoulders are the junction of the collarbone, shoulder blade, and upper arm. This requires dense layers of muscle and connective tissue to perform movements and support the joint. However, when there is trauma and poor mechanics, it can lead to dysfunction, pain, and reduced mobility.</p>



<p>Today, we will discuss shoulder mobility exercises. We cover the proper technique, shoulder anatomy, tips, and a mobility routine to enhance shoulder mobility and function.</p>



<div class="wp-block-group ft-snippet is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<p class="has-medium-font-size">7 Shoulder Mobility Exercises</p>



<p>These are the 7 best shoulder mobility exercises for improving flexibility and function.</p>



<ul>
<li><a href="#Dynamic-Arm-Swing">Dynamic Arm Swing.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Doorway-Chest-Stretch">Doorway Chest Stretch.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Overhead-Triceps-Stretch">Overhead Triceps Stretch.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Cable-Shoulder-Internal-Rotation">Cable Shoulder Internal Rotation.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Cross-Body-Shoulder-Stretch">Cross-Body Shoulder Stretch.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Dumbbell-Scapular-External-Rotation">Dumbbell Scapular External Rotation.</a></li>



<li><a href="#Arm-Circle">Arm Circle.</a></li>
</ul>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">7 Best Shoulder Mobility Exercises</h2>



<p>These are the seven best shoulder mobility exercises. Below we list a technique guide and tips to enhance your mobility for this joint.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dynamic-Arm-Swing">Dynamic Arm Swing</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dynamic-arm-swing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dynamic arm swing</a> is effective for warming up our shoulder muscles and joints and increasing mobility. By swinging the arms across the midline of our body, we warm up and lengthen the pectoralis, deltoid, and rotator cuff muscles.&nbsp;</p>



<p>This makes them great for upper-body training and as part of an <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/at-home-shoulder-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">at-home shoulder workout</a>.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Dynamic Arm Swings" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980224572?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dynamic Arm Swing Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Standing with your arm beside your body, with your feet shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Lift your arms out to your side away from your body so they are parallel to the floor.</li>



<li>Inhale, and engage your core muscles.</li>



<li>Exhale, and swing your arm toward the midline of your body, allowing them to cross over.</li>



<li>From here, inhale and swing them outward, returning them to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your arm straight and relaxed, using the momentum to swing continuously.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale as you swing your arms across your body, and inhale as you swing outward.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>



<p>Perform the swings in a dynamic motion to help <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6370952/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">reduce passive stiffness</a>.</p>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th>Duration</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1–2</td><td>30–60 seconds</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1–2</td><td>30–60 seconds</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1–2</td><td>30–60 seconds</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1–2</td><td>30–60 seconds</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Dynamic Arm Swing</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Doorway-Chest-Stretch">Doorway Chest Stretch</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/doorway-chest-stretch" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">doorway chest stretch</a> is excellent for lengthening the chest and shoulder muscles. Due to our sedentary lifestyle, our chest muscles can become tight, affecting our posture.&nbsp;</p>



<p>When we place our arms on the doorway, our chest and shoulder muscles are encouraged to lengthen. This improves our ability to open the chest and maintain an upright posture.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Doorway Chest Stretch" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980232454?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Doorway Chest Stretch Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Standing in a doorway with your feet shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Lift your arms to the side and place your hand, forearm, and elbow on the door.</li>



<li>With a proud chest, inhale, and engage your core.</li>



<li>Exhale and gently lean forward until you feel a stretch across your chest.</li>



<li>From here, inhale, and lean back to the starting position.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Focus on breathing during the stretch. Exhale as you lean forward, and inhale as you lean back. This will help you relax into the stretch.</li>



<li>Keep your chest up for the duration of the stretch. This will help you lengthen the chest muscles.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
<figure class="wp-block-table table-custom h-title table-border" style="font-size:16px;font-style:normal;font-weight:500"><table class="has-fixed-layout"><thead><tr><th class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center"><p class="pri-color-1">Training Style</p></th><th class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left"><p class="pri-color-1">Sets</p></th><th>Duration</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Strength Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1–2</td><td>30–60 seconds</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Hypertrophy</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1–2</td><td>30–60 seconds</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Endurance Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1–2</td><td>30–60 seconds</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Power Training</td><td class="has-text-align-left" data-align="left">1–2</td><td>30–60 seconds</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps of Doorway Chest Stretch</figcaption></figure>
</div></div>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Overhead-Triceps-Stretch">Overhead Triceps Stretch</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/overhead-triceps-stretch" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">overhead triceps stretch</a> allows us to lengthen the triceps and enhance shoulder mobility. Our long head of triceps is on the inner side of the arm and helps to stabilize the shoulder. The overhead triceps stretch allows us to lengthen the long head of the tricep. Furthermore, bending the elbow stretches the lateral and medial heads.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe title="Overhead Triceps Stretch" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980214574?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Overhead Triceps Stretch Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Standing, reach both of your hands directly over your head.</li>



<li>Bend the elbow of your left arm, placing the palm of your left hand at the base of your neck.</li>



<li>Using your right hand, reach over and hold your left elbow.</li>



<li>Inhale, engage your core.</li>



<li>Exhale, and gently pull your left elbow toward the midline of the body, gradually increasing the stretch.</li>



<li>Inhale, release, and switch sides.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Inhale, then exhale as you pull the elbow toward the midline of the body. This can <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30133419/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">promote relaxation</a> and help you relax into the stretch.</li>



<li>To intensify the stretch, increase the bend in the elbow of the stretching arm. Aim to place the palm at the base of the neck, and reach toward the same side shoulder blade.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
