<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Cable-Shoulder-Internal-Rotation">Cable Shoulder Internal Rotation</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/cable-shoulder-internal-rotation" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">cable shoulder internal rotation</a> is an isolation exercise that strengthens the rotator cuff of the shoulder. This exercise helps improve shoulder stability and control.</p>



<p>The cable shoulder internal rotation safely overloads the shoulder muscles, making it one of the great <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/exercises-for-shoulder-pain" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">exercises for shoulder pain</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Cable Shoulder Internal Rotation" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/981903834?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Cable Shoulder Internal Rotation Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Adjust the cable pulley to elbow height and attach a single grip handle.</li>



<li>Grab the handle on the side closest to the machine, holding it with a neutral grip.</li>



<li>Tuck your elbow to your side and bend the elbow at a 90-degree angle.</li>



<li>Turn your body so the cable is pointing toward your shoulder.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Your torso should be angled at a 90-degree angle to the pulley, with feet shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Inhale, and engage your core muscles.</li>



<li>Exhale, and rotate the inward toward the midline of the body.</li>



<li>From here, inhale, and return the arm to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your elbow tucked to your side for the duration of the set. This will improve your ability to target the internal rotators.</li>



<li>Focus on breathing, and engaging your core. This will increase rigidity through your torso, improving your capacity to target the internal rotators.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



