<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Cross-Body-Shoulder-Stretch">Cross-Body Shoulder Stretch</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/cross-body-shoulder-stretch" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">cross-body shoulder stretch</a> lengthens the back of the shoulder and upper back muscles. Its primary focus is to stretch the posterior deltoid, rotator cuff, and rhomboids. This makes it great for improving flexibility and shoulder mobility.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Across Chest Shoulder Stretch" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/980247106?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Cross-Body Shoulder Stretch Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Standing with your feet shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>With your left hand reach it across your body to the opposite shoulder.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Use your right hand to pull the arm close to your body.</li>



<li>Inhale, and engage your core.</li>



<li>Exhale, and gently pull your left arm toward your chest.</li>



<li>Inhale, and release. Repeat on the right side.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Stand upright with a proud chest. This will improve your ability to stretch the posterior deltoid, rotator cuff, and upper back.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Focus on your breathing, inhaling before the stretch, and exhaling as you pull the arm toward the chest. This will help you relax into the stretch.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



