<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Scapular-External-Rotation">Dumbbell Scapular External Rotation</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-scapular-external-rotation" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell scapular external rotation</a> is an isolation exercise that strengthens the rotator cuff, improving shoulder function and stability. Consider adding it to the beginning or during your <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/upper-body-workout-for-women" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">upper body workout</a> to improve shoulder strength and function.    </p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="72341201-Dumbbell-Standing-Scapular-External-Rotation-(male)_Back_" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/988714391?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Scapular External Rotation Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Standing, grab a pair of dumbbells and hold them by your side.</li>



<li>With your elbows tucked to your side, bend the elbows to a 90-degree angle.</li>



<li>Rotate the dumbbells so your palms are facing upward.</li>



<li>Gently pull your shoulder blades back to make a proud chest.</li>



<li>Inhale, and engage your core muscles.</li>



<li>Exhale, and rotate your arms outward, gently pulling your shoulder blades together.</li>



<li>Rotate until your forearms are pointed outward at a 45-degree angle.</li>



<li>From here, inhale, and rotate your arms inward, returning them to the starting position.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your chest up for the duration of the set. This will improve your ability to engage the rotator cuff and trapezius.</li>



<li>Ensure your elbows are tucked to your side for the duration of the set. This allows for great rotator cuff activation.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



