<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Shoulders</h2>



<p>Our shoulder joint or <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537018/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">glenohumeral joint</a> is the junction of the collarbone, scapula, and humerus (arm bone). A ball and socket joint, it is capable of an incredible range of motion. This requires connective tissue to encapsulate the joints, and muscles to provide movement and stability.</p>


