<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Anterior Deltoid</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537056/#:~:text=The%20deltoid%20originates%20from%20the,deltoid%20tuberosity%20of%20the%20humerus." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">anterior deltoid</a> makes up the front of the shoulder. It originates from the front of the collarbone and inserts into the humerus. It brings the arm in front and above the body.</p>



<p>When the anterior deltoid is shortened, or restricted, it can impair our range of motion. Exercises such as arm circles, arm swings, and chest doorway stretches are all great for lengthening the anterior deltoid. This will improve the range of motion and increase shoulder mobility.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Lateral Deltoid</h3>



<p>The lateral deltoid is on the outer side of the shoulder. It attaches from the shoulder blade, or scapula, and inserts into the humerus. It lifts the arm out to the side of the body and provides stability to the shoulder.</p>



<p>This lateral deltoid works alongside the anterior and posterior deltoid to perform many of the shoulder movements. This means that it requires adequate strengthening and flexibility to maintain correct shoulder mobility.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Posterior Deltoid</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/rear-delt-bodyweight-exercises" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">posterior deltoid</a> occupies the back of the shoulder. It originates from the scapula and inserts into the humerus. It extends the arm back and stabilizes the shoulder. </p>



<p>To lengthen the posterior deltoid, you can perform the cross-body stretch. To strengthen and improve function, perform the dumbbell scapula external rotation.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Supraspinatus</h3>



<p>Our <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537202/#:~:text=The%20supraspinatus%20has%20associations%20with,humerus%20at%20the%20glenohumeral%20joint." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">supraspinatus</a> is on the top of your shoulder blade. It originates from the top of the scapula and inserts into the top of the humerus. It abducts the arm and stabilizes the shoulder.</p>



<p>The supraspinatus is part of the rotator cuff, a group of muscles that stabilize the shoulder and control fine movement. They are essential for all shoulder-based exercises and movements.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Infraspinatus</h3>



<p>Your <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30020627/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">infraspinatus</a> is below the infraspinatus. It originates from the back of the scapula and is inserted into the humerus. It externally rotates and abducts the humerus, and stabilizes the shoulder. Like the supraspinatus, the infraspinatus is part of the rotator cuff and is vital for all our shoulder movements.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Teres Minor</h3>



<p>Our <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK513324/#:~:text=The%20teres%20minor%20lies%20inferior,deep%20to%20the%20deltoid%20muscle." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">teres minor</a> is below our infraspinatus. It attaches from the outer side of the scapula to the humerus. It externally rotates the arm and stabilizes the shoulder. This small muscle works alongside the supraspinatus and infraspinatus to stabilize the ball and socket joint through all shoulder movements.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Subscapularis</h3>



<p>Your <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK513344/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">subscapularis</a> is between the scapula and rib cage. It attaches from the underside of the scapula to the humerus. It internally rotates, adducts, or brings the humerus to the side of the body, and stabilizes the shoulder. The subscapularis is the final rotator cuff muscle.&nbsp;</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Benefits Of Shoulder Mobility Exercises</h2>



<p>Shoulder mobility exercises are fantastic for improving range of motion, mobility, and shoulder health.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Prevents Injuries</h3>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="1250" height="700" src="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Prevents-Injuries.jpg" alt="Prevents Injuries" class="wp-image-23126" srcset="https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Prevents-Injuries.jpg 1250w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Prevents-Injuries-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Prevents-Injuries-1024x573.jpg 1024w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Prevents-Injuries-768x430.jpg 768w, https://www.endomondo.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Prevents-Injuries-150x84.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" /><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Shoulder mobility exercises help restore the range of motion and optimize function. <span>Photo: ALEXSTUDIO/Freepik</span></figcaption></figure>



<p>Injury prevention is a combination of progressively loading muscle tissue and improving mobility and flexibility to enhance movement patterns. <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8139277/#:~:text=Results,of%20injury%20reccurence%206.4%20times." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Low-quality movement patterns</a> have been associated seven times greater risk of injury.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The exercises above are prime examples of injury prevention exercises. These help restore the range of motion and optimize function. Consider combining them with our <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/best-shoulder-workout-for-mass" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">best shoulder workout for mass</a>, to improve your shoulder health.&nbsp;</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Increases Range Of Motion&nbsp;</h3>



<p>Increasing the range of motion requires a combination of flexibility, mobility, and strength training. <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC8067745/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Stretching and strength training</a> have been shown to increase the range of motion. Meanwhile, static stretching has been shown to <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2411-5142/8/2/37#:~:text=Eight%20of%20the%20studies%20within,38%2C39%2C40%5D." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">increase the range of motion</a>.</p>



<p>Static stretches such as the doorway chest stretch, cross-body stretch, and overhead tricep stretch are excellent for increasing range motion.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Improves Flexibility</h3>



<p>Improving flexibility requires lengthening of muscle tissue to its full range of motion for a designated time. This can be done both using static holds or dynamic movements. This has been shown to have a positive impact on <a href="https://www.mdpi.com/2673-995X/3/1/10" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">muscle strength</a>, power, and hypertrophy.</p>



<p>The shoulder mobility exercises above are excellent examples of static and dynamic stretches, which enhance flexibility.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Safety Tips&nbsp;</h2>



<ul>
<li>Avoid stretching into pain or through pain. Stretching beyond pain can <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC9157514/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">increase ranges of motion</a>, however, we recommend only doing this with a professional.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Concentrate on breathing during your stretch. Research indicates that controlled, synchronized breathing can help promote relaxation and reduce tension.</li>



<li>During the dumbbell scapula external rotation and cable internal rotation, focus on tensing our muscles. This will improve your <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26700744/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">mind-muscle connection</a>, enhancing your results.</li>



<li>Ensure that you perform a warm-up before doing your shoulder mobility exercises. Warm-ups increase muscle tissue temperature and blood flow, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5833972/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">improving exercise performance</a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
</ul>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Conclusion</h2>



<p>Shoulder mobility exercises are excellent for increasing flexibility, and range of motion, and preventing injury. Simple to perform, they can positively impact your training, while enhancing your function, resulting in a better quality of life.&nbsp;</p>



<p>If you want to improve your shoulder mobility and performance, add these movements to your workout. This will help you gradually improve your function and your training results.</p>



