<h2 class="wp-block-heading faq-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1623393125914"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Why is shoulder mobility so important?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">The quality of our movement has been linked to a decrease in injury. Therefore, increasing mobility can reduce the risk of injury, and improve our quality of life.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1724948619104"><strong class="schema-faq-question">W<strong>hat are the benefits of shoulder rotation exercises?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Shoulder rotation exercises strengthen our rotator cuff, improving mobility and function. They can improve our shoulder health.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1724948620096"><strong class="schema-faq-question">What causes poor shoulder mobility?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Poor shoulder mobility can be caused by pain, trauma, poor posture, and mechanics. The shoulder joint has many layers of muscle and connective tissue. When they are damaged, it can lead to dysfunction, decreasing our mobility.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1724948621172"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can I do shoulder mobility workouts every day?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Yes. Shoulder mobility, flexibility, and strengthening exercises require little recovery.</p> </div> </div>
</div></div>
